@startuml
' --- whole-map provenance: cycle that introduced each @id ---
' @cycle(DOM-TEST-EVIDENCE, 0025)
' @cycle(DOM-TEST-PHASE-RECORD, 0025)
' @id(DOM-TEST-EVIDENCE)
' @desc(DOM-TEST-EVIDENCE, "The per-cycle red->green evidence artifact (.mdd/cycles/<N>/test-evidence.yml), a first-class cycle file. TestEvidence { version, cycle, gap_tests: Vec<GapTest> }; GapTest { id, model_id, layer, red: Option<PhaseRecord>, green: Option<PhaseRecord> }. The red phase writes `red`; the green step writes `green`. Because by close the test is green, the recorded RED is the only proof it failed first — so the artifact, not prose, is what the non-negotiable gate verifies. mdd validates its SHAPE (parses; every gap @id present; each phase well-formed); the actual fail/pass is produced by agent-Bash running the test (same plan/execute split as deploy).")
' @id(DOM-TEST-PHASE-RECORD)
' @desc(DOM-TEST-PHASE-RECORD, "One observation of running a gap test in a phase (PhaseRecord): { command, exit_code, result (Fail|Pass), excerpt, at }. It stores the runner's OWN output — the command, its exit code, and a captured excerpt — not a bare boolean, so a recorded RED is hard to fabricate without actually running (the §4 locked decision; a pre-implement git ref was considered and not adopted). The red phase requires an assertion/expectation failure (inspected in `excerpt`), not a compile/collection error; otherwise it is surfaced for confirmation. red.result must be Fail (exit_code != 0); green.result must be Pass (exit_code == 0).")
' Current-side domain for Cycle C: the evidence artifact and its
' per-phase record. Pure data; the running that fills it is agent-Bash,
' the gate that reads it is deterministic.
title MDD diagram-driven tests — red->green evidence (current)

enum TestPhaseResult {
  Fail
  Pass
}

class PhaseRecord {
  + command : String
  + exit_code : i32
  + result : TestPhaseResult
  + excerpt : String
  + at : String
}

class GapTest {
  + id : String
  + model_id : String
  + layer : TestLayer
  + red : Option<PhaseRecord>
  + green : Option<PhaseRecord>
}

class TestEvidence {
  + version : u32
  + cycle : String
  + gap_tests : Vec<GapTest>
}

TestEvidence "1" o-- "*" GapTest : records >
GapTest "1" --> "0..1" PhaseRecord : red >
GapTest "1" --> "0..1" PhaseRecord : green >
PhaseRecord ..> TestPhaseResult : result >

note bottom of PhaseRecord
  DOM-TEST-PHASE-RECORD: the runner's own command +
  exit_code + excerpt, not a boolean — so RED is
  verifiable. red => Fail (exit!=0); green => Pass (exit==0).
end note
@enduml
